
<h2>
    The Box Model
</h2>

<p>
    Each box model in CSS contains a:
    <ul>
        <li>
            margin box
        </li>
        <li>
            border box 
        </li>
        <li>
            padding box 
        </li>
        <li>
            content box 
        </li>
    </ul>
    <img alt="Box Model Example" width="310" height="249" src="~/lib/Resources/css-box-outline.png" /> 
    <figcaption>
        Box Model Example
    </figcaption>
</p>

<p>
    The margin box is on the outside and every other element is nested inside it. 
    The border is the next layer, wrapping around the padding of the content box. 
</p>
<p>
    The content box is where the information is placed: text, images and so on. 
</p>

<!-- Margin Box -->
<div class="rounded-3" style="margin-left: 3%; border: 2px dashed black; max-width: 300px;">
    <!-- Border -->
    <div style="max-width: 300px; border: 1px solid rgb(242, 197, 148); background: rgb(242, 197, 148);">
        <!-- Padding -->
        <div class="text-center" style="max-width: 300px; border: 20px solid rgb(247, 217, 144); margin: 20px; padding: 20px; background: rgb(185, 203, 124);">
            <!-- Content -->
            - <span style="border: 1px solid black; background: rgb(132,172,182)">Content Box</span> -            
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

