<h2>
    margin box
</h2>
<p>
    The margin box contains the margin which is the outer shell surrounding 
    the element. The red box below represents the margin of the content box. 
</p>
<!-- Margin Box -->
<div class="rounded-3" style="margin-left: 3%; border: 2px dashed black; max-width: 300px;">
    <!-- Border -->
    <div class="rounded-3" style="max-width: 300px; border: 1px solid rgb(242, 197, 148); background: red; ">
        <!-- Padding -->
        <div class="text-center" style="max-width: 300px; border: 20px solid rgb(247, 217, 144); margin: 20px; padding: 20px; background: rgb(185, 203, 124);">
            <!-- Content -->
            - <span style="border: 1px solid black; background: rgb(132,172,182)">Content Box</span> -            
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<figcaption style="margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 3%;">
    Margin-box is the red
</figcaption>
<pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    margin: 10px; /* Apply to all sides */
    /* margin-left: 10px; */
    /* margin-right: 10px; */
    /* margin-top: 10px; */
    /* margin-center: 10px; */
}
</code></pre>
<figcaption style="margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 3%;">
    Margin Example
</figcaption>
<p>
    Margin is the space around an element and its neighbors. Learn more 
    about margin <a asp-controller="Css" asp-action="Margins">here</a>. 
</p>

<h2>
    border box
</h2>
<p>
    The border-box represents the border of the element: a rectangle of color 
    that wraps the element, but is still inside the margin-box. Borders are fully 
    customizable with CSS.  
</p>
<!-- Margin Box -->
<div class="rounded-3" style="margin-left: 3%; border: 2px dashed black; max-width: 300px;">
    <!-- Border -->
    <div style="max-width: 300px; border: 1px solid rgb(242, 197, 148); background: rgb(242, 197, 148);">
        <!-- Padding -->
        <div class="text-center" style="max-width: 300px; border: 20px solid red; margin: 20px; padding: 20px; background: rgb(185, 203, 124);">
            <!-- Content -->
            - <span style="border: 1px solid black; background: rgb(132,172,182)">Content Box</span> -            
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<figcaption style="margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 3%;">
    Border-box in red
</figcaption>

<pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    border: 10px solid red; /* Apply to all sides */
