<h2>
    content box
</h2>
<p>
    The content box holds the text of the element. It is the main content. This can 
    be images, text, buttons, icons, etc..
</p>
<!-- Margin Box -->
<div class="rounded-3" style="margin-left: 3%; border: 2px dashed black; max-width: 300px;">
    <!-- Border -->
    <div style="max-width: 300px; border: 1px solid rgb(242, 197, 148); background: rgb(242, 197, 148);">
        <!-- Padding -->
        <div class="text-center" style="max-width: 300px; border: 20px solid rgb(247, 217, 144); margin: 20px; padding: 20px; background: rgb(185, 203, 124);">
            <!-- Content -->
            - <b><span style="border: 1px solid black; background: red">Content Box</span></b> -            
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

